{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775853511032,"sessionID":"ses_286e2102fffeK1Ugk0qqEpAss1","part":{"id":"prt_d791e1b76001rU8xGnff8R1NED","messageID":"msg_d791e09d4001Xxye7bKMqj8U21","sessionID":"ses_286e2102fffeK1Ugk0qqEpAss1","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-007/spec.yaml"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-007/spec.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: AR-007\n2: title: K8s Reconciler 控制器\n3: module: pkg/workloadmanager\n4: language: Go\n5: size: L\n6: status: open\n7: \n8: # AR-007: K8s Reconciler 控制器\n9: # Module: pkg/workloadmanager\n10: # Language: Go\n11: # Size: L\n12: \n13: # OpenSpec Metadata\n14: openspec:\n15:   version: \"1.0\"\n16:   project: agentcube\n17: \n18: # Architecture Requirement\n19: requirement:\n20:   type: reconciler-controller\n21:   description: |\n22:     Implement the Kubernetes Reconciler controller for the WorkloadManager.\n23:     This controller watches AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRs, reconciles\n24:     their desired state with actual cluster state, and manages the lifecycle\n25:     of sandbox resources. It integrates with the controller-runtime framework\n26:     and provides event-driven reconciliation with proper error handling and\n27:     exponential backoff.\n28: \n29: # Scope\n30: scope:\n31:   in:\n32:     - CRD resource watchers for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter\n33:     - Reconciliation loop implementation with controller-runtime\n34:     - Event-driven reconciliation on resource changes\n35:     - Exponential backoff for failed reconciliations\n36:     - Finalizer handling for graceful deletion\n37:     - Status updates and condition management\n38:     - OwnerReference management for garbage collection\n39:     - Integration with existing WorkloadManager service layer\n40:     - Reconcile queue with rate limiting\n41:     - Metrics and observability hooks\n42:   out:\n43:     - CRD type definitions (handled in AR-001/AR-002)\n44:     - client-go generated code (handled in AR-003)\n45:     - HTTP service framework (handled in AR-004)\n46:     - Sandbox creation/deletion logic (handled in AR-005/AR-006)\n47:     - Multi-cluster reconciliation (separate AR)\n48:     - Leader election for HA (separate AR)\n49: \n50: # Acceptance Criteria\n51: acceptance:\n52:   - Controller watches AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRs\n53:   - Reconciliation loop processes create/update/delete events\n54:   - Exponential backoff for transient failures (configurable)\n55:   - Finalizers ensure graceful resource cleanup\n56:   - Status conditions accurately reflect resource state\n57:   - OwnerReferences are properly set for garbage collection\n58:   - Integration with WorkloadManager service layer\n59:   - Metrics exposed for reconciliation latency and errors\n60:   - Unit tests achieve >= 80% coverage\n61:   - Integration tests verify end-to-end reconciliation\n62: \n63: # References\n64: references:\n65:   - AR-001: CRD AgentRuntime Types\n66:   - AR-002: CRD CodeInterpreter Types\n67:   - AR-003: client-go Generated Code\n68:   - AR-004: WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework\n69:   - AR-005: Sandbox Creation Handler\n70:   - AR-006: Sandbox Deletion and Lifecycle Management\n71: \n72: # Estimation\n73: estimation:\n74:   size: L\n75:   story_points: 8\n76:   days: 5\n\n(End of file - total 76 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: AR-007\ntitle: K8s Reconciler 控制器\nmodule: pkg/workloadmanager\nlanguage: Go\nsize: L\nstatus: open\n\n# AR-007: K8s Reconciler 控制器\n# Module: pkg/workloadmanager\n# Language: Go\n# Size: L\n\n# OpenSpec Metadata\nopenspec:\n  version: \"1.0\"\n  project: agentcube\n\n# Architecture Requirement\nrequirement:\n  type: reconciler-controller","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-007/spec.yaml","time":{"start":1775853510997,"end":1775853511029}}}}
